# Copy to frontend/.env.local for local dev. Vite only exposes vars prefixed
# with VITE_ to the browser bundle (import.meta.env). Never put secrets here —
# a Cognito User Pool ID and public App Client ID are not secrets, but anything
# in a frontend bundle is world-readable, so put nothing sensitive here.
#
# These identify the SAME Cognito User Pool the backend verifies tokens against
# (see backend/README.md for how to create it). The App Client ID here must be
# the public SPA client (created with --no-generate-secret) and must allow SRP
# auth (ALLOW_USER_SRP_AUTH), which amazon-cognito-identity-js uses.

VITE_COGNITO_USER_POOL_ID=us-east-1_XXXXXXXXX
VITE_COGNITO_CLIENT_ID=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
VITE_COGNITO_REGION=us-east-1

# Base path for API calls. Defaults to /api (proxied to the backend in dev via
# vite.config.ts; served through CloudFront in prod). Override only if needed.
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=/api
